properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 13 at 1:41AM MST until January 14 at 11:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 35 to 45 MPH with gusts up to 65 MPH.

* WHERE...Interstate 80 between Rawlins and Laramie, including
Arlington and Elk Mountain.

* WHEN...Now until 11 AM MST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will
create dangerous travel conditions for light and high profile
vehicles, including camping and tractor trailers.
properties.instruction:
A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of
58 mph or more can lead to property damage.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 AM MST TUESDAY
